<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>What is dojo management software?</h3>

<p>Dojo management software is a specialised platform for traditional martial arts schools. It handles student databases, kyu/dan rank tracking, grading ceremonies, class scheduling, and billing while using terminology and workflows appropriate to the dojo environment rather than generic gym language.</p>

<h3>How is dojo software different from gym software?</h3>

<p>Dojo software is purpose-built for martial arts operations. It includes belt rank progression tracking, testing eligibility automation, curriculum management, and grading ceremony coordination—features absent from generic gym platforms. It also uses appropriate terminology (students vs members, dojo vs facility, sensei vs trainer).</p>

<h3>Can dojo software track multiple martial arts?</h3>

<p>Yes, quality dojo software supports multiple disciplines with separate rank tracks. A school teaching both Karate and Judo can maintain independent belt progressions, testing schedules, and curriculum requirements for each art while sharing student accounts and billing.</p>

<h3>How does testing management work?</h3>

<p>Testing management includes automatic eligibility determination based on attendance and time-in-rank, test scheduling with capacity limits, student registration and fee collection, grading panel assignment, results recording, certificate generation, and automatic rank updates upon passing.</p>

<h3>What should dojo software cost?</h3>

<p>Dojo management software typically costs £50-200 per month depending on student count and features. Smaller dojos (under 100 students) often find suitable options at £50-80 monthly, while larger schools with advanced features may pay £150-200. Per-student pricing models charge £1-3 per active student.</p>

<h3>Can I import my existing student records?</h3>

<p>Most dojo software accepts data imports from spreadsheets or other platforms. You can typically import student contact information, rank history, membership details, and attendance records. Allow 1-2 weeks for data migration and verification.</p>

<h3>Do students get their own login?</h3>

<p>Yes, student portals provide individual access for viewing schedules, tracking rank progress, managing payments, and communicating with instructors. Parents receive portal access for youth student accounts, allowing them to monitor progress and handle administrative tasks.</p>

<h3>How does family billing work?</h3>

<p>Family accounts link related students under shared billing. The system automatically applies sibling discounts, consolidates invoices, and allows parents to manage payments for multiple children from a single dashboard while maintaining individual progress tracking for each student.</p>

